# Monstera Helm Chart – Project Overview

**Monstera** is a self-hosted ActivityPub server written in Go that exposes the Mastodon-compatible REST API. Application repo: [chairswithlegs/monstera](https://github.com/chairswithlegs/monstera).

**This repo** contains only the Helm chart. Chart root is `chart/` (Chart.yaml, values.yaml, templates).

## Chart layout

- **Server**: API deployment + Service + PVC for media when `media.driver: local`. Sensitive config comes from a single Secret that the user is expected to provide -- the chart does **not** create it. Set `server.existingSecret` to the name of the Secret.
- **UI**: Next.js static frontend served by nginx (Deployment, Service, ConfigMap).
- **Migration**: Optional migration Job using the same server image and Secret, controlled by `migrationJob.enabled`.
- **Subcharts**: Optional PostgreSQL (Bitnami) and NATS. When disabled, the user supplies their own and sets `DATABASE_URL` / `NATS_URL` in the server Secret.
